dslRuleAfterChange:
A conceptual rule (not valid DSL syntax as of now) might look like:

// Generify List method return types based on inferred usage
$Type $methodName($params$) :: $Type is raw and $methodName returns a collection that implies a generic type
=> $Type<inferGenericType($methodName)> $methodName($params$)
;;

// Generify raw collection variable declarations based on inferred usage
$Type $var = new $Type($args$);
=> $Type<inferGenericType($var)> $var = new $Type<inferGenericType($var)>($args$);
;;

(Note: `inferGenericType` is a placeholder for a hypothetical DSL function)

/* Rule for modifying the ternary expression (partially implementable) */
$resolver.hasTypeName() ? $resolver.getKey().toCharArray() : org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.util.CharOperation.concatWith($resolver.compoundName(), '.') :: sourceVersionGE(9)
=> $resolver.hasTypeName() ? $resolver.getKey().toCharArray() : ($resolver.hasModuleName() ? $resolver.moduleName() : org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.util.CharOperation.concatWith($resolver.compoundName(), '.'))
;;

/* Conceptual rule for adding the 'else if' branch (requires DSL extension) */
// This pattern would need to match the 'else if' block and insert a new one after it.
// Example (not valid DSL syntax for insertion):
// else if ($element instanceof org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.TypeParameter)
// 	$key = ((org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.TypeParameter) $element).getKey(true);
// => ... original else if ...
// else if ($element instanceof org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.BinaryModule)
// 	$key = ((org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.BinaryModule) $element).getKey(true);
// ;;

throw new java.lang.ClassCastException()
=> throw new java.lang.ClassCastException($childClass + " is not an instance of " + $nodeType)
;;

// Note: This rule is illustrative and depends on future DSL capabilities to capture and inject local variables.
// The pattern itself would need to be expanded to bind $childClass and $nodeType for this to be meaningful.

this.setModifiers(moduleDecl.annotations(), moduleDeclaration.annotations, moduleDeclaration.sourceStart)
=> 
List<org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.IExtendedModifier> modifiers = new java.util.ArrayList<>();
this.setModifiers(modifiers, moduleDeclaration.annotations, moduleDeclaration.sourceStart);
for (org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.IExtendedModifier ie : modifiers) {
    if (!ie.isAnnotation()) {
        continue; // not setting to malformed.
    }
    moduleDecl.annotations().add(ie);
}
;;

